		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.superfamicom.org/snes/show/Registers">http://wiki.superfamicom.org/snes/show/Registers</a><!-- m --> <br /><br />On this website I found this under registers $2180-$2183<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">This means you could use DMA mode 4 to $2180 and a table in ROM to write any sequence of RAM addresses. The value does not wrap at page boundaries on increment.</div><br /><br />Is this true?  Can you DMA from rom into wram with these registers?  If so, then using a CPU RAM buffer would be possible.  The only problem I see is that it wouldn't work for decompressed sprites, because you can't do wram-to-wram DMAs.

		

		</td>
